config.user_prompt_template:
Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}

Message from DP:
{{message}}

Extract any vehicle registration number (e.g. MH12AB1234) or transaction reference number from the message. Set has_identifier to true if at least one is found, false otherwise. If not found, return empty strings for the identifier fields.

config.structured_output_schema:
{
  "type": "object",
  "title": "IdentifierExtraction",
  "required": [
    "has_identifier",
    "vehicle_number",
    "reference_number"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "has_identifier": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "True if a vehicle number or reference number was found"
    },
    "vehicle_number": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Vehicle registration number if found, else empty string"
    },
    "reference_number": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Transaction reference number if found, else empty string"
    }
  },
  "additionalProperties": false
}

config.user_prompt_template:
Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
DP message: {{message}} 

The DP has not provided a vehicle registration number or transaction reference number. Write a short, friendly reply asking them to share one so we can retrieve the policy copy for them. 

Reply message example:- 
Hi, could you please share your vehicle registration number or transaction reference number? This will help us quickly retrieve your policy copy. Thanks!

Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
DP Message: {{message}}

The policy copy has been successfully located, and ownership has been verified.

Write a short, friendly, and professional response confirming that:
- The policy copy has been shared with the DP
- The request has been successfully resolved

Reference the policy Copy ID: {{mis_result.policy_copy}}


Reply Example Formate:

Hi, your policy copy has been successfully retrieved and shared with you. The request has been completed and resolved.

Policy Copy ID: {{mis_result.policy_copy}}

Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
DP message: {{message}}

The ownership details need manual verification. Write a short, professional message telling the DP their request has been escalated and the team will get back to them shortly.

Reply example formate:-

Hi, your request has been escalated for manual verification of ownership details. Our team will review it and get back to you shortly. Thank you for your patience.

Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
DP message: {{message}}

The policy was transacted recently (less than 3 hours ago) and the copy is still being generated. Write a short, friendly message telling the DP the document will be available within 3 hours of the transaction time and to check back shortly.


Reply example formate:-

Hi, your policy was transacted recently and the document is currently being generated. It will be available within 3 hours of the transaction time. Please check back shortly. Thank you!

Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
DP message: {{message}}

The policy copy has not been generated even though more than 3 hours have passed since the transaction. Write a short, empathetic message telling the DP that their request is being prioritised and the team will resolve it as soon as possible.

Reply example formate:-

Hi, we understand the delay and sincerely apologize for the inconvenience. Your request is being prioritised, and our team is working to resolve it as soon as possible. Thank you for your patience.
